    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-hake-with-mediterranean-style-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong>, <strong>diced onion</strong>, <strong>halved cherry tomatoes </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-hake-with-mediterranean-style-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Chop your <strong>capers</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-hake-with-mediterranean-style-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>chopped capers</strong>, <strong>chopped parsley </strong>and <strong>remaining chopped garlic </strong>in a bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong>, <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>salsa verde</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-hake-with-mediterranean-style-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, add a handful of <strong>flour</strong> to a plate with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> flour mixture</strong></p><p>Pat your <strong>hake fillet[s]</strong>\u00a0dry with kitchen<strong> </strong>paper</p><p>Add the <strong>hake fillet[s] </strong>to the floured plate and turn several times until fully coated \u2013 this is your <strong>coated hake</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-hake-with-mediterranean-style-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated hake</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-hake-with-mediterranean-style-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Stir your <strong>balsamic sun-dried tomato paste </strong>and <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>through the <strong>tomato rice </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>sun-dried tomato rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-hake-with-mediterranean-style-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pan-fried hake</strong> over the <strong>sun-dried tomato rice</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>salsa verde </strong>all over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
